-- China central bank chief: cut reliance on rating agencies
-- 
-- Sat Dec 24, 2011 9:15pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/12/25/us-china-cbank-ratings-idUSTRE7BO00K20111225

 

 BEIJING  (Reuters) - China's Central Bank Governor Zhou Xiaochuan said financial companies must cut their reliance on ratings agencies, and that China is considering setting up a system where investors pay for ratings, rather than bond issuers. 
 Zhou was speaking at a forum in Beijing. (Reporting by Aileen Wang and Koh Gui Qing)